rComments: The topics discussed are very interesting and inspirational. Prof Arviv does a very good job of addressing some of the wrong beliefs that are common in the society.

D-level classes in UTSC require participation in the classes anyways. Arviv's a fair marker imo, and he won't bore you to death. His lectures are interesting because it's not him talking all the time and he's good at giving feedback.

Excellent prof, great lectures that are always interesting. The topics he covers and his critical analysis are very relevant and important. All students should take this course! There no tricks, just lots of valuable learning!

Lectures are dense but straight-forward and easy to follow, average amount of readings for a 200 course (about 45ish pages a week). Very understanding professor and a fair grader. Genuinely enjoys teaching.

Responds to emails at any hour, and is always willing to talk if you have a problem with assignments or material. Smart guy and is passionate about the topics discussed. Looking forward to another class with him  next semester.
Tons of reading but plenty of time to do it.

Lectures weren't bad but also weren't great. Lecture style was unstructured, lack of power points or any visual aids. While concepts were engaging, classroom time felt dull as it was mostly group discussions. Grading system was clear and fair. Overall, a nice man that's there if you need the help, but course structure seemed somewhat unfinished.

Assignments are pretty easy, recommends doing the readings though they really aren't necessary just need to find a line or two to use in assignments. Class is incredibly straight forward, attendance isn't super important, most concepts can be found online. Boring lecturer, and incredibly left wing to the point where you question his teaching

When he's good at lecturing, he's good. Though in times when things he mumbles over his won words and end his sentences assuming that what he's saying was understood.  The course touches on the same ideas over and over again, and the readings are long but mandatory for the assignments. Overall, the course is fine, listen and manage your time wisely
teacherRatingTags: ['So many papers', 'Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy']
